## ⭐ What Is the Use of the New Features Added?

### 1️⃣ body: — Why We Use It?
`body:` is the main area of the screen.  
Whatever you want to show on the page (text, image, buttons) must be placed inside `body:`.

Without body → screen will look empty.

---

### 2️⃣ Column — Why We Use It?
`Column` arranges widgets **one below another** (vertical layout).

Example:  
Photo  
↓  
Name  
↓  
Profession

---

### 3️⃣ CircleAvatar — Why We Use It?
`CircleAvatar` displays a **round profile picture**.  
Perfect for:
- Profile apps  
- Business cards  
- Contact list  
- Portfolio UI  

It makes the UI look **professional and clean**.

---

### 4️⃣ Text("Praneeth") — Why We Use It?
Used to display your **name** on the screen.  
Styling (font, size, color) makes it attractive.

---

### 5️⃣ Text("Mobile App Developer") — Why We Use It?
This shows your **job role / profession** under your name.  
The `letterSpacing` makes the text stylish.

---

### 6️⃣ Background Color — Why We Use It?
Sets the **theme color** of your screen.  
Teal color makes the profile look modern and clean.

---

Flutter naming rules →  
Class names must start with **Capital Letters** (Best Practice).  
Makes your code look **clean, professional, readable**.



===========================================================================
Entire code :


import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main(){
runApp(Myapp());
}

class Myapp extends StatelessWidget {
  const Myapp({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: Scaffold(
        backgroundColor:Colors.teal,
        body: Column(
          children: [
            CircleAvatar(
              backgroundImage: AssetImage("images/corizo.png"),
              radius: 100,
              ),

              Text("Praneeth",
              style: TextStyle(
                color: Colors.white,
                fontSize: 24,
                fontFamily:"Script"
 
              ),),

              Text("Mobile App Developer",
              style: TextStyle(
                color: Colors.white,
                fontSize: 24,
                letterSpacing: 5
 
              ),)
          ],
          )
      ),
    );
  }
}
